# 🔷 📁 MINI PROJECT 1

## 📌 Title  

# 🔷 Handling Multiple Fact Tables Without Synthetic Keys in Qlik Sense

## 📌 Overview
This project demonstrates how to design a scalable Qlik Sense data model by handling multiple fact tables while avoiding synthetic keys and circular references.

---

## ❗ Problem Statement
When multiple fact tables share common fields (e.g., PAT_ENC_ID), Qlik automatically generates synthetic keys, leading to:
- Ambiguous relationships
- Incorrect aggregations
- Poor performance

---

## 🧠 Solution Approach
- Identified common key: `PAT_ENC_ID`
- Avoided direct joins between fact tables
- Used `EXISTS` logic to control data association
- Renamed and structured fields to prevent unintended links

---

## 🛠️ Implementation

### Sample Logic
```qlik
PAT_VISIT:
SELECT *
FROM Clinical_Datamart.dbo.PAT_VISIT A
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT DISTINCT PAT_ENC_ID
    FROM NLP_Datamart.dbo.QUERY_ALERT_RESULTS B
    WHERE A.PAT_ENC_ID = B.PAT_ENC_ID
);
